      • loadProducts

        private void loadProducts()
                   throws java.io.IOException,
                          java.lang.ClassNotFoundException
        Method that loads the Products from the files. t checks if the .obj file exists and if it does, it loads the products from it. If it doesn't, it loads the products from the default .txt file.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if we can't write to the file.
        java.lang.ClassNotFoundException - if the object file doesn't exist.

      • addProduct

        private void addProduct​(Product product)
                 throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Method that adds a new product to the list of products. It checks if a product is already in the available products, if it's not adds it.
        Parameters:
        product - Name The name of the product to be found.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the product is already in the list of products.

      • removeProducts

        public void removeProducts​(Product p,
                           int nr)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        Method that removes a product X times given as parameter, from the list of products. If there is none in stock, it removes it from the available products overall.
        Parameters:
        p - product The product to be removed.
        nr - Number of times the product is to be removed.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if we can't write to the file.
